      "acceptanceCriteria": "Order-of-accuracy verification using manufactured solutions for Navier-Stokes and hemolysis transport equations; documented convergence rates.",
      "rationale": "Order-of-accuracy study performed for momentum equations only; hemolysis transport equation not verified via manufactured solution. Observed convergence rate 1.7 vs. expected 2.0 for velocity. Achieved level 2 against required level 4."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "GCI below 5% for all hemolysis-relevant QoIs on at least three mesh refinement levels; Richardson extrapolation applied.",
      "rationale": "GCI computed on three meshes. Velocity and pressure GCI within 3%, but shear-stress-derived hemolysis index GCI reaches 8.4% on finest practical mesh. Richardson extrapolation not applied to hemolysis QoI. Achieved level 2 against required level 4."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
